h1.p:
The most common species, valued for their unusual foliage, include the panda plant (

 Kalanchoe tomentosa

); penwiper plant (

 K. marmorata

); velvet leaf, or felt bush (

 K. beharensis

); and devil’s backbone, or mother of thousands (

 K. daigremontiana

). A range of attractive potted plants, commonly known as florist’s kalanchoe and distinguished by their colourful flowers, have been derived from

 K. blossfeldiana;

they are marketed widely in the winter for their flowers, which may remain fresh for as long as eight weeks.
